@startuml
title Tool Execution Lifecycle - Parallel Execution, Ordered Context

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 130
skinparam defaultFontName Georgia
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam TitleFontSize 19
skinparam TitleFontColor #161616
skinparam NoteFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowColor #5E5A53
skinparam activity {
  BackgroundColor #F2E9D9
  BorderColor #1D1D1D
  FontColor #161616
  ArrowColor #5E5A53
  StartColor #8C2721
  EndColor #161616
  DiamondBackgroundColor #F5EBDD
  DiamondBorderColor #8C2721
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F5EBDD
  BorderColor #8C2721
  FontColor #7B1E1E
}

start

:Receive assistant tool_use blocks (ordered);
:Partition by concurrency safety;

if (streaming executor?) then (yes)
  :Queue into StreamingToolExecutor;
  :Apply permission + interrupt rules;
  :Run eligible tools in parallel;
  :Emit progress / synthetic errors;
  :Yield finished results in safe order;
else (batch)
  if (batch concurrency-safe?) then (yes)
    :Run in parallel;
    :Buffer modifiers;
    :Replay modifiers in block order;
  else (serial)
    :Run one by one;
    :Apply each modifier immediately;
  endif
endif

:Merge tool_result into transcript;
:Return deterministic context to query loop;
stop

note right
  Harness controls that live
  around every tool call:
  permission gates,
  interrupt behavior,
  sibling cancellation,
  synthetic tool_results.
  Execution may be parallel.
  Context evolution is always
  replayed in block order.
end note

@enduml
